result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old) and Operating w/PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old) and the other charge, Operating w/PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Julia E Liekis was found guilty of OWI (3rd w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old), an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: THE DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS SHALL DEDUCT RESTITUTION AND ALL OTHER COURT OBLIGATIONS AT THE RATE OF 25% OF ALL MONIES RECEIVED WHILE INCARCERATED.
If the defendant's probation is revoked, the conditions of extended supervision shall remain the same as the conditions of probation.

miscConds.notes:
Pay $2,400.00 fine and costs, with all but $1,200.00 is stayed.    **NOTE: THE DEFENDANT IS ORDERED TO PAY ALL COURT OBLIGATIONS TO THE CLERK OF COURTS OFFICE.   Payment is due within 30 days.  If the Defendant cannot make the payment, he/she must report to the Clerk of Courts Office to set up a payment plan.  Failure to comply will result in other collection methods including a civil Judgment and/or suspension of your drivers license for two (2) years.  This judgment may be collected by income assignment if you fail to pay fines and costs as ordered.
------------------------------------

Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge.
------------------------------------

Defendant must follow all OWI Court program, jail and probation rules with no violations. Any violation of rules or failure to adhere to treatment requirements could mean removal from the OWI court program, revocation of probation, and an immediate imposition of a jail sentence. Such sentence must be served within the Walworth County Huber facility.
------------------------------------

Mandatory attendance of Victim Impact Panel (VIP).
------------------------------------

Conditions of participation will include drug/alcohol screens and complete meaningful compliance with ALL treatment programming and attendance at OWI Court sessions. This includes a requirement of no alcohol or drug use.

timeConds.notes: Initial mandatory minimum jail sentence to be completed at the Walworth County Jail Huber Facility. This conditional jail time may be served on electronic monitoring at the discretion of the Walworth County Jail.
